strings.Value: "I'm glad I didn't grow up among the barbarians. Look at them! Childhood in the tribe is almost worse than slavery!"
"You talk about things you don't know anything about... but I don't have nothing to compare it with either."
"Let's leave the past in the past. Whatever has happened, it's given us what we have now... and we're all right now, aren't we?"
"Childhood is the time of powerlessness, helplessness, and naivety. But the days of youth..."
"I don't know what's worse – to lose one's tribe as a young child, or to grow up in it as an outsider."
